        <updateDate>2023-12-08T15:03:05Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;b&gt;National Guard and Reservists Debt Relief Extension Act of 2023&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This bill extends for an additional four years the exemption from the presumption of abuse means test under Chapter 7 (liquidation) bankruptcy for qualifying members of an Armed Forces reserve component or the National Guard. Specifically, members who, after September 11, 2001, are called to active duty or to perform a homeland defense activity for not less than 90 days qualify for this exemption. Currently, the exemption expires on December 19, 2023. &lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
